        <body>     	      
            
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="01"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <p>
                    <lb n="1"/>matirai koṇṭa kōpparakēcaripanma<ref>r</ref>kki yāṇṭu mu<supplied reason="lost">ppattu</supplied>       	
                    <lb n="2"/> Eṭṭ<surplus>ā</surplus>-Āvatu </p> <p> kuṉṟa-kūṟṟattu Avani-ka<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice>taṟpa-<hi rend="grantha">Īśva<supplied reason="omitted">ra</supplied>gṛha</hi>ttu <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character" precision="low"/>
                        <lb n="3" break="no"/>ṭai Ittaḷi vaṇṇa
                    </p>
                
            </div>
            
            <div type="apparatus"/>            	               
            
            
            <div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">
                <p>Fortune! Prosperity! <supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the <supplied reason="subaudible">38th</supplied> year of Kōpparakesarivarman who has taken
Madurai <gap reason="ellipsis"/> of the temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gṛhattu</foreign></supplied> of the Lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>īśvara</foreign></supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Avanikaṉtaṟpa,<note>That is,
Kaṉtaṟpa upon earth.</note> a <foreign>devadāna</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, <gap reason="ellipsis"/> the checking of coins and
gold <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaṇṇa</foreign><note>That is, unfinished <foreign>vaṇṇakku</foreign>?</note></supplied> of this temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ittaḷi</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="ellipsis"/></p>
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p n="01"><foreign><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi></foreign>. This phrase is at the beginning of the line on the pilaster, on the left of the main text, possiby later added. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Gillet2024_01"/></bibl>: <quote><foreign>svasti śrī</foreign> is added on the pilaster.</quote></p>
                <p n="1"><bibl><ptr target="bib:Gillet2024_01"/></bibl>: <quote>The date is most probably 38: <foreign>mu<supplied reason="lost">ppattu</supplied> eṭṭu āvatu</foreign>. Thus, we may supply about four letters at the end of each line of <ref target="DHARMA_INSMelKil00003"/> and <ref target="DHARMA_INSMelKil00004"/>#4.</quote></p>
                <p n="3">The inscription is unfinished.</p>
            </div>
            
